  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Agricultural Revitalization of Tsaghkunq and Geghamavan Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Agricultural Revitalization of Tsaghkunq and Geghamavan Communities Project will improve the livelihoods and economic competitiveness of farmers through the introduction of the integrated dairy production and farm management model. The project&#x2019;s objectives are to improve the socioeconomic conditions of the target rural population through increasing the efficiency and productivity of rural economies, increase the income of the target population by linking them to the market, and promote youth leadership development by establishing a Youth Club. The project will target 600 families and 200 youth throughout the project timeframe. Project families will receive barley seeds to establish their own livestock feed crops for improved animal nutrition. Participating farmers&#x2019; animals (approximately 780 in total) will be artificially inseminated to improve dairy yields. The project will establish a milk collection unit, which will ensure access of the farmers to markets and sustainable income sources through market link establishment with dairy processors. This integrated approach is designed to enhance advanced farming and production techniques and to ensure competitiveness of project participant families. The establishment of the Youth Club will ensure rural youth integration into the social and economic life of the community.</narrative>
  </description>
